public class CodedEntry
extends VAnnotation
Coded Entry is a component of a clinical statement that includes the name of the coded system, the code name, and the code value. This is where one would put in UMLS, SNOWMED, ICD and similar encodings. Updated by JCasGen Thu Aug 18 18:15:19 EDT 2022 XML source: C:/Users/divitag2/work/softwareRepos/bodyFunction/project/60_03_type-descriptors/target/jcasgen/typesystem.xml
